SEARCH
Package org.efs.dispatcher.config

Class EfsDispatcherConfig

java.lang.Object
org.efs.dispatcher.config.EfsDispatcherConfig
public final class EfsDispatcherConfig extends Object
EfsDispatcher configuration definition. Contains all the properties required to build an EfsDispatcher. This class is defined as a typesafe configuration bean.

Please note that this class may only be used to configure efs dispatchers and not special dispatchers.

Example EfsDispatcherConfig File Enty

For further explanation on what these properties mean and valid settings, see the property set method (e.g. setSpinLimit(long)). 
dispatcherName = AlgoDispatcher
threadType = SPINPARK
numThreads = 3
priority = 8 // Thread.MIN_PRIORITY ≤ priority < Thread.MAX_PRIORITY
spinLimit = 1000000
parkTime = 500 nanos
eventQueueCapacity = 256
maxEvents = 64
runQueueCapacity = 8
Author:
Charles W. Rapp

    • setEventQueueCapacity

      public void setEventQueueCapacity(int capacity)
      Sets efs agent event queue capacity. This capacity is applied to each efs agent associated with this dispatcher.

      capacity should be a 2 power value. If not, event queue capacity is set to the next 2 power value > given capacity.

      Parameters:
      capacity - agent event queue capacity.
      Throws:
      com.typesafe.config.ConfigException - if capacity < EfsDispatcher.MIN_EVENT_QUEUE_SIZE.

    • setRunQueueCapacity

      public void setRunQueueCapacity(int capacity)
      Set efs dispatcher agent queue capacity.

      The capacity should be a 2 power value. If not, event queue capacity is set to the next 2 power value > given capacity.

      Parameters:
      capacity - agent queue capacity.
      Throws:
      com.typesafe.config.ConfigException - if capacity ≤ zero.

    • setMaxEvents

      public void setMaxEvents(int maxEvents)
      Sets maximum number of events an efs agent associated with this dispatcher may process when dispatched. This is done to prevent an agent from unfairly dominating a dispatcher. Note: there is no limit to this value and may be set to Integer.MAX_VALUE.
      Parameters:
      maxEvents - agent may process up to this many events at a time.
      Throws:
      com.typesafe.config.ConfigException - if maxEvents ≤ zero.
